# ide-agents architecture

Local CLI + HTTP server + React UI for managing **IDE agents and skills** from git repos via **symlinks** (Cursor adapter in MVP).

## Layout

```
ide-agents/          # npm package name; repo folder may differ
├── src/             # Node backend + CLI (tsc → dist/)
├── web/             # Vite + React + Mantine UI (→ web/dist/)
├── docs/            # Docusaurus site (separate package)
└── fixtures/        # sample git repo for manual testing
```

## Runtime flow

1. `ide-agents` (cli.ts) reads `~/.ide-agents/config.json`, starts Fastify on `127.0.0.1:3921`.
2. Production: Fastify serves `web/dist` + `/api/*`. Dev: Vite :5173 proxies `/api` → backend.
3. Git clones live in `~/.ide-agents/repos/<slug>/`.
4. UI toggles **Global** / **Project** (mutually exclusive) → immediate `PUT /installations` + `POST /apply`.
5. `apply.ts` creates/removes symlinks via enabled IDE adapters (`cursor`, `claude`, `codex`). Never overwrite non-symlink targets.

## Key modules

| Module | Role |
|--------|------|
| `config.ts` | read/write config, migrate `~/.agentdesk/` → `~/.ide-agents/` |
| `git.ts` | clone, fetch, pull, status |
| `scan.ts` | list `skills/*/SKILL.md`, `agents/*.md`, parse frontmatter |
| `targets.ts` | check if symlink target path is blocked |
| `apply.ts` | symlink create/remove |
| `adapters/` | map installation → IDE config dirs (`~/.cursor/`, `~/.claude/`, `~/.codex/`, project `.agents/` for Codex) |
| `server.ts` | REST API |

## Config schema (v1)

`installations[]`: `{ repoId, kind, artifactId, global, project, projectPath }`. One record per artifact per repo.

Skill frontmatter `scope: global | project | any` controls which toggles are enabled in UI.

## Conventions

- ESM, Node 20+, TypeScript strict in `src/`.
- API errors: `{ error: string }`.
- macOS/Linux only (v0.1). Single adapter: `cursor`; more IDE adapters later.
- Do not add corp/private skills to this repo — only generic tooling.
